a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes a b c d :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re 5) (Im 0)"
and h1 : "b = Complex (Re 3) (Im (-1))"
and h2 : "c = Complex (Re 3) (Im 0)"
and h3 : "d = Complex (Re 5) (Im (-1))"
shows  "a * b + c * d = Complex (Re 18) (Im 10)"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Simplify $5(3-i)+3i(5-i)$. The final Answer is 18+10i
 ### Proof
 $5(3-i) + 3i(5-i) = 15-5i + 15i - 3i^2 = 15 +10i -3(-1) = \boxed{18+10i}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes a b c d :: complex
assumes h0 : "a = Complex (Re 5) (Im 0)"
and h1 : "b = Complex (Re 3) (Im (-1))"
and h2 : "c = Complex (Re 3) (Im 0)"
and h3 : "d = Complex (Re 5) (Im (-1))"
shows  "a * b + c * d = Complex (Re 18) (Im 10)"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Calculate the sum of the product of the complex numbers (5 + 0i) and (3 - i), and the product of the complex numbers (3 + 0i) and (5 - i). The final answer is (18 + 10i).
